steps.description:
Choose the best possible mode of communication to reach anyone who might be interested. Try multiple channels if possible. If you are organizing a work group, use company email. {"smallUrl":"https://www.wikihow.com/images/thumb/2/2d/Facilitate-a-Group-Step-1Bullet1.jpg/v4-460px-Facilitate-a-Group-Step-1Bullet1.jpg","bigUrl":"https://www.wikihow.com/images/thumb/2/2d/Facilitate-a-Group-Step-1Bullet1.jpg/v4-760px-Facilitate-a-Group-Step-1Bullet1.jpg","smallWidth":460,"smallHeight":345,"bigWidth":760,"bigHeight":570,"licensing":"<div class="mw-parser-output"><p>License: <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-nc-sa/3.0/">Creative Commons</a><br>
</p><p><br />
</p></div>"}

If you are organizing a school group, ask for telephone numbers or emails. Also, research a school LISTSERV to encourage new membership. {"smallUrl":"https://www.wikihow.com/images/thumb/7/7b/Facilitate-a-Group-Step-1Bullet2.jpg/v4-460px-Facilitate-a-Group-Step-1Bullet2.jpg","bigUrl":"https://www.wikihow.com/images/thumb/7/7b/Facilitate-a-Group-Step-1Bullet2.jpg/v4-760px-Facilitate-a-Group-Step-1Bullet2.jpg","smallWidth":460,"smallHeight":345,"bigWidth":760,"bigHeight":570,"licensing":"<div class="mw-parser-output"><p>License: <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-nc-sa/3.0/">Creative Commons</a><br>
</p><p><br />
</p></div>"}

If you are hosting a church group, make sure the meeting time is in the church bulletin. {"smallUrl":"https://www.wikihow.com/images/thumb/2/2c/Facilitate-a-Group-Step-1Bullet3.jpg/v4-460px-Facilitate-a-Group-Step-1Bullet3.jpg","bigUrl":"https://www.wikihow.com/images/thumb/2/2c/Facilitate-a-Group-Step-1Bullet3.jpg/v4-760px-Facilitate-a-Group-Step-1Bullet3.jpg","smallWidth":460,"smallHeight":345,"bigWidth":760,"bigHeight":570,"licensing":"<div class="mw-parser-output"><p>License: <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-nc-sa/3.0/">Creative Commons</a><br>
</p><p><br />
</p></div>"}

If you are starting a support group, post the information at hospitals, online and in counselor/doctor offices. {"smallUrl":"https://www.wikihow.com/images/thumb/c/c1/Facilitate-a-Group-Step-1Bullet4.jpg/v4-460px-Facilitate-a-Group-Step-1Bullet4.jpg","bigUrl":"https://www.wikihow.com/images/thumb/c/c1/Facilitate-a-Group-Step-1Bullet4.jpg/v4-760px-Facilitate-a-Group-Step-1Bullet4.jpg","smallWidth":460,"smallHeight":345,"bigWidth":760,"bigHeight":570,"licensing":"<div class="mw-parser-output"><p>License: <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-nc-sa/3.0/">Creative Commons</a><br>
</p><p><br />
</p></div>"}

Starting and ending meetings require an outspoken person who will keep track of time and any remaining agenda items. Wear a watch and refer back to it occasionally to make sure you are on track. Announce the start and end time in your communication with group members. Also, consider announcing topics and the time structure so that members can adequately prepare. {"smallUrl":"https://www.wikihow.com/images/thumb/1/13/Facilitate-a-Group-Step-3Bullet1.jpg/v4-460px-Facilitate-a-Group-Step-3Bullet1.jpg","bigUrl":"https://www.wikihow.com/images/thumb/1/13/Facilitate-a-Group-Step-3Bullet1.jpg/v4-760px-Facilitate-a-Group-Step-3Bullet1.jpg","smallWidth":460,"smallHeight":345,"bigWidth":760,"bigHeight":570,"licensing":"<div class="mw-parser-output"><p>License: <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-nc-sa/3.0/">Creative Commons</a><br>
</p><p><br />
</p></div>"}

One important structure to announce is whether it is an open group and whether the group has “cross-talk.” This means that the group can discuss, rather than just sharing an opinion when it is their turn. {"smallUrl":"https://www.wikihow.com/images/thumb/c/ce/Facilitate-a-Group-Step-3Bullet2.jpg/v4-460px-Facilitate-a-Group-Step-3Bullet2.jpg","bigUrl":"https://www.wikihow.com/images/thumb/c/ce/Facilitate-a-Group-Step-3Bullet2.jpg/v4-760px-Facilitate-a-Group-Step-3Bullet2.jpg","smallWidth":460,"smallHeight":345,"bigWidth":760,"bigHeight":570,"licensing":"<div class="mw-parser-output"><p>License: <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-nc-sa/3.0/">Creative Commons</a><br>
</p><p><br />
</p></div>"}
